<span id="freeTextContainer8419529834569145756">Before &quot;A Mercy&quot; came out, I had only read &quot;Beloved&quot;, &quot;The Bluest Eyes&quot; maybe a year before. (I was out of the country for two years during the 70&apos;s --I don&apos;t remember reading much of anything during that time), when Toni Morrison had first established herself as a writer &apos;to read&apos; -- A woman making a difference in the world! <br/><br/>Her writing is deeply felt --(reminding me --I&apos;ve 2 other books in my house still &apos;to-read&apos;).<br/>&quot;Sula&quot; and her later book &quot;Love&quot;. <br/><br/>Her books about slavery reach deep below the </span>
  <span id="freeText8419529834569145756" style="display:none">Before "A Mercy" came out, I had only read "Beloved", "The Bluest Eyes" maybe a year before. (I was out of the country for two years during the 70's --I don't remember reading much of anything during that time), when Toni Morrison had first established herself as a writer 'to read' -- A woman making a difference in the world! <br /><br />Her writing is deeply felt --(reminding me --I've 2 other books in my house still 'to-read').<br />"Sula" and her later book "Love". <br /><br />Her books about slavery reach deep below the surface --- but in all her books she tells a powerful story --(be it about a child, or a mother, or other voices in the community) --Toni Morrison, [awarded Nobel Prize in Literature], --is a humanitarian who inspires us all to look at ourselves --and speak out when its not easy to do so --<br />Being the stand for justice! </span>
